<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2009-08-12</DATELINE><TITLE>Use of Revised International Health Regulations during Influenza A (H1N1) Epidemic, 2009</TITLE><BODY>Strong international health agreements and good planning created a structure and common procedure for nations involved in detection and evaluation of the emergence of influenza A (H1N1). This report describes a timeline of events that led to the determination of the epidemic as a public health emergency of international concern, following the agreed-upon procedures of the International Health Regulations. These events illustrate the need for sound international health agreements and should be a call to action for all nations to implement these agreements to the best of their abilities.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>